{
  "_comment": [
    "Team-owned reference data. This file is the JSON twin of the core.Ref* tables",
    "in bp-sql-layer. The web pipeline (tools/build-dashboard-data.mjs) reads it",
    "instead of the SQL tables so the mock/demo path needs no database.",
    "KEEP THE TWO IN STEP: a change here should be mirrored in 07_seed_reference.sql.",
    "",
    "HUB & SPOKE: the CoE hub owns this file, the grade rate card and the per-VDI",
    "class rates. Each spoke owns its propositions, processes (grade + SMV) and",
    "its VDIs. spokeId on a resource = the spoke whose infra pool it belongs to;",
    "null = hub-owned (test/dev machines), which lands in the shared hub pool.",
    "",
    "SPOKE COLOURS: colorLight/colorDark are the spoke's accent on each surface.",
    "The set was validated for CVD separation and contrast on both dashboard",
    "surfaces (dataviz six-checks) — if you change one, re-validate the set.",
    "",
    "HUMAN COST / SMV MECHANISM: a process carries the GRADE of colleague whose",
    "manual work it displaces plus the SMV (standard minutes value) per case.",
    "gradeRates is the date-effective rate card: benefit is valued at the rate in",
    "force on each item's outcome date, so a pay award never re-values history.",
    "Spokes with different FTE grades simply reference different grade codes.",
    "",
    "HUB TEAM COST: peopleCostHistory (ownerId='HUB') is the SOLE source of truth",
    "for the hub's people run-rate used in cost calculation. estateCostHistory's",
    "teamAnnualCostGBP field is retained for schema parity with bp-sql-layer's",
    "core.RefEstateCostHistory table only — it is NOT read for cost calculation.",
    "estateCostHistory now only supplies workingDaysPerYear/productiveHoursPerDay/",
    "effectiveFrom/note. peopleCostHistory also carries one informational record",
    "per spoke (ownerId = spokeId as a string) — these are NOT wired into the cost",
    "engine; the architecture only ever charges spoke INFRA cost, never spoke",
    "people cost, into the estate economics.",
    "",
    "VDI RENEWAL / COVERAGE WINDOW: each resource now carries renewalDate (the",
    "annual renewal anchor date; cycles tile every 365 days from it, both forward",
    "and backward), an optional annualCostGBP override (bypasses the costClass",
    "rate when set), an optional licenseExpiryDate (last day of licensed cover),",
    "and status ('active'|'retired'). Outside a VDI's coverage window it costs",
    "£0 AND has zero available capacity that day — see src/reference/economics.ts",
    "for the exact algorithm (mirrored byte-for-byte in build-dashboard-data.mjs",
    "and verify-economics.mjs)."
  ],

